    "summary": "Oil prices are rising Monday following the latest fighting to threaten the U.S.-Iran ceasefire, but Wall Street isn’t very worried, and U.S. stocks are hanging near their records.  The S&P 500 added 0.3% to its all-time high set on Friday.  The majority of U.S. stocks fell, and some of the worst performers were companies with big fuel bills hurt by the rise in oil prices.",
